INSTALLATION under GAP
--
In your gap project ...

1. Install
    bin/gap install -e 'git+https://github.com/fragaria/gap-resources'

2. Add routes to src/routes.py
    routes = (
        ...
        include('/_my_resources_base_url', 'lib/resources
        ...
    )

3a. Register your models in src/routes.py

    from myapp.models import MyModel
    from resources import register
    register(MyModel)

3b. Register models for whole package
    
    Open src/config.py and add RESOURCES_AUTODISCOVER with list of modules where resources should look for models.
    
    Example:
        RESOURCES_AUTODISCOVER = [
            'app.myapp.models',
        ]

4. Start your app and list your project on
    http://localhost:8080/_my_resources_base_url/mymodel

other urls are (relative to _my_resources_base_url)
    GET ./  ... list objects with fields description
    GET ./describe  ... full description
    POST ./<id>  ... updates existing object (and returns its data)
    POST ./   ... creates new object (and returns it)

